PREHISTORIC EXTINCTIONS DUE TO DISEASE? (03)
============================================
[see
Prehistoric extinctions due to disease? 970502115854
Prehistoric extinctions due to disease? (02) 970502192317]
[1]
Date: Fri, 02 May 97 18:04:33 -0500
From: "Dr. Jose Campione"<dr._jose_campione_at_paho/cec@cclink.paho.org>
> The proponents of the disease hypothesis ... propose to test it by
examining fossils for sequences of the genomes of the pathogens mentioned.
But since the test depends on primers from exisiting disease agents, if the
pathogens responsible for the extinctions have also died out it will be
impossible to get results.
>
Difficult yes but not impossible. They could try something like the
representational difference analysis (RDA) proposed by Lisitsyn et al.
(Science 259:946, 1993) using as normal genome a library from earlier fossil
remains of the same species. This kind of technology has already been
successfully applied to the discovery of new viruses (i.e., KSHV) (Science
266: 1865, 1994).
